        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 14 at 5:48PM EDT by NWS Upton NY</headline>
        <description>At 548 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Voluntown, or near Jewett City, moving southwest at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Jewett City, Griswold, Preston, Lisbon, Voluntown, and North
Stonington.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
